<DOC><DOCNO> AP880604-0079 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-04-88 0904EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Nigeria-Crash     06-04 0171</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Nigeria-Crash,0181</SECOND><HEAD>Air Force MiG Crashes Into Police Barracks, Killing Pilot AndPolicemen</HEAD><DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Nigerian air force MiG crashed into apolice barracks near an air base and killed 12 people, includingthe pilot, the military said today.   Newspapers said at least 21 others were badly burned.   The air force's logistics command said the Soviet-made fighterplane crashed into the administrative building of the NigeriaPolice ``C'' division in Makurdi on Friday night.   The pilot, six policemen, and several civilians died, thecommand said in a statement. The civilians had come to the stationto file complaints, it said.   The statement did not give any other details.   The 30-year-old plane burst into flames near the city of Makurdibefore crashing, the newspapers said. They said more than 20 otherpolicemen and a child were badly burned.   A major air base is located at Makurdi, 370 miles northeast ofLagos.   No other details were immediately available.   Nigeria's air force has at least two versions of the MiG-21.</TEXT></DOC>